    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, a true pinnacle of Japanese engineering. The heart of this machine is a meticulously maintained 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression and surgical power delivery. The complex vacuum-actuated turbo transition remains seamless, providing linear torque through the entire rev range. This example retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the legendary 50:50 weight distribution is fully realized on the tarmac. With zero structural oxidation and a cockpit devoid of typical bolster wear or dash lift, this FD is mechanically and aesthetically flawless. A rare opportunity for the purist seeking uncompromised rotary performance.",
      "price": 44500.0,
